mruby
------------------------------------------
mruby is the lightweight implementation of the Ruby language complying to
(part of) the ISO standard. mruby can be linked and embedded within your
application. We provide the interpreter program 'mruby' and the interactive
mruby shell 'mirb' as examples. You can also compile Ruby programs into
compiled byte code using the mruby compiler 'mrbc'. All those tools reside in
'bin' directory. The 'mrbc' is also able to generate compiled byte code in a C
source file. You can check the 'mrbtest' program under the 'test' directory.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.3.1-1
  libreadline7-6.3.8-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  make-4.1-1
  ruby-2.2.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/mruby/mruby

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/mruby/mruby/archive/1.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mruby-1.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mruby-1.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mruby-1.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mruby-1.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mruby)
  /usr/bin/mirb.exe
  /usr/bin/mrbc.exe
  /usr/bin/mrdb.exe
  /usr/bin/mruby-strip.exe
  /usr/bin/mruby.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mruby.README
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/LEGAL
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/MITL
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/TODO
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/compile.md
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/debugger.md
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/gc-arena-howto.md
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/mrbconf.md
  /usr/share/doc/mruby/mrbgems.md

